  "doc_id": "58727",
  "text": "The assay was carried out as described previously [CITATION_1] . In brief, HUVECs were seeded in 6 well plates till the formation of a confluent monolayer after which a wound was created using 200 μl micropipette tip. The detached cells were removed by washing with PBS and the plates were treated with (MBA). The wounds were photographed after 12 and 18 h, and the width of the cell-free wounds was measured using an inverted light microscope supplied with Leica Quin computerized imaging system. Ten fields per well were photographed and minimum of 30 readings per field were taken. The results are presented as mean percentage of migration inhibition compared to control ± SD, (n = 3).",
